(553, 3, 'page', '{\"_token\":\"N3zbGy9IaGSIwsyXdd5ildctMFz8BtWe9IWBnDod\",\"name\":\"School Bus\",\"slug\":\"school-bus\",\"slug_id\":\"98\",\"model\":\"Botble\\\\Page\\\\Models\\\\Page\",\"description\":\"Saigon Star has a fleet of twelve minibuses which are used to collect and drop off children in most areas of the city.\",\"content\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:26px;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">School Bus<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:center\\\"><img alt=\\\"\\\" height=\\\"533\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/sgstar.edu.vn\\/storage\\/general\\/transports-2c.jpg\\\" width=\\\"644\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Saigon Star has a fleet of twelve minibuses which are used to collect and drop off children in most areas of the city. Currently, we operate a bus service for families in District 1, 2, 3, 4, 7, 9, Thu Duc, Binh Thanh, Phu Nhuan &amp; Go Vap. Application for the bus service should be made at the time of registration or before the beginning of the school year. However, if space is available, families may apply for this service during the school year. Bus routes are designed to minimise the amount of time the children spend on the bus. Therefore, door to door service is not always possible. Students are supervised by a teacher or teaching assistant at all times and will only be handed over to a pre-designated adult.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"gallery\":null,\"seo_meta\":{\"seo_title\":null,\"seo_description\":null},\"submit\":\"save\",\"language\":\"en_US\",\"ref_from\":null,\"status\":\"published\",\"template\":\"default\",\"image\":null}', 'updated', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/80.0.3987.122 Safari/537.36', '14.241.249.67', 3, 14, 'School Bus', 'primary', '2020-03-01 21:15:15', '2020-03-01 21:15:15'),
(554, 3, 'page', '{\"_token\":\"N3zbGy9IaGSIwsyXdd5ildctMFz8BtWe9IWBnDod\",\"name\":\"Our Shared Vision & Mission\",\"slug\":\"our-shared-vision-mission\",\"slug_id\":\"101\",\"model\":\"Botble\\\\Page\\\\Models\\\\Page\",\"description\":\"Our Shared Vision & Mission\",\"content\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><strong><span style=\\\"color:#16a085;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:24px;\\\">Our Mission &amp; Shared Vision<\\/span><\\/span><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong><span style=\\\"color:#16a085;\\\">Our Shared Vision:<\\/span><\\/strong><b>&nbsp;<\\/b>Responsible global citizens<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#16a085;\\\"><b>Our Mission<\\/b>:<\\/span> To provide a safe and supportive learning environment, and every opportunity for children to be successful both as learners and as contributors in a changing world.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#16a085;\\\"><b>Our Shared Vision &amp; Mission Explained<\\/b><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Beyond the influence of parents in the home, a child&rsquo;s education is the single most important factor in determining the type of person a child will become;&nbsp;&nbsp;that is why it is a school&rsquo;s &lsquo;shared vision&rsquo; is so important when choosing a school.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Regarding our mission, this can be broken down into two parts: for children to be safe and successful.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We define <span style=\\\"color:#16a085;\\\">&lsquo;<b>safe<\\/b>&rsquo;<\\/span> as being both physically safe and emotionally safe. We define <span style=\\\"color:#16a085;\\\">&lsquo;<b>successful<\\/b>&rsquo; <\\/span>as experiencing daily success in learning, making meaningful contributions to society, and developing the attitudes and skills of a lifelong learner.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"gallery\":null,\"seo_meta\":{\"seo_title\":null,\"seo_description\":null},\"submit\":\"save\",\"language\":\"en_US\",\"ref_from\":null,\"status\":\"published\",\"template\":\"default\",\"image\":null}', 'updated', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/80.0.3987.122 Safari/537.36', '14.241.249.67', 3, 17, 'Our Shared Vision & Mission', 'primary', '2020-03-01 22:15:48', '2020-03-01 22:15:48'),
