(4, 'Tuyển giáo viên(nước ngoài)', 'Ho Chi Minh, Viet Nam', 'thương lượng', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">C&Aacute;C PH&Uacute;C LỢI D&Agrave;NH CHO BẠN</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">- Bảo hiểm lao động v&agrave; bảo hiểm y tế theo luật ph&aacute;p Việt Nam.<br />\r\n- Th&aacute;ng lương 13<br />\r\n- Kh&aacute;m sức khỏe định k&igrave;.</span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">M&Ocirc; TẢ C&Ocirc;NG VIỆC</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">- Số lượng: 5&nbsp;nh&acirc;n vi&ecirc;n<br />\r\n- Dậy học theo gi&aacute;o tr&igrave;nh quốc tế IPC&nbsp;;<br />\r\n- L&ecirc;n kế hoạch v&agrave; b&agrave;i giảng dậy học cho học sinh</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Y&Ecirc;U CẦU C&Ocirc;NG VIỆC</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">- Tốt nghiệp chuy&ecirc;n ng&agrave;nh sư phạm<br />\r\n- Độ tuổi từ 22- 55&nbsp;tuổi<br />\r\n- Hiểu văn h&oacute;a Việt Nam<br />\r\n- Kh&aacute;t khao đạt được c&aacute;c mục ti&ecirc;u lớn.<br />\r\n- Si&ecirc;ng năng, ki&ecirc;n tr&igrave;, trung thực.</span></span></p>', 'published', '2019-11-30 19:56:50', '2020-02-28 21:43:02'),
(5, 'Our Hiring Process ', 'Our Hiring Process ', 'Negotiable', '<p><span style=\"font-size:24px;\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\"><b>Information guides for prospective teachers</b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1oPdFLlHov_OytlXM9BNuny4dRMq8WfEo/view\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;New Teacher Welcome Pack</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;<a data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1GMUmjG-cWy423JfaqwRg3HPMt2BqxwogGQBNRrHQZ1s/edit?usp%3Dsharing&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1582375143413000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGakQ0udgMqGRcJBsnDpYpHB8Wd_g\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1GMUmjG-cWy423JfaqwRg3HPMt2BqxwogGQBNRrHQZ1s/edit?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\">School Events</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-&nbsp;<a data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1OoGM6XnaKPXcXyd1IBY-5ahpD08O03afKV5kL3DybVs/edit?usp%3Dsharing&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1582375143413000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFqEoWxkNQkaaDy74qSxFbtQPiiWw\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1OoGM6XnaKPXcXyd1IBY-5ahpD08O03afKV5kL3DybVs/edit?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\">Cost of Living</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;-<a data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://drive.google.com/open?id%3D1pY6j0Olk2pbtViWhuFx2JeUa3RDxQvq4&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1582375143428000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGLtpi0kHH8yNcOPZKhmBiaIdcJWw\" href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=1pY6j0Olk2pbtViWhuFx2JeUa3RDxQvq4\" target=\"_blank\">Accommodation</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\"><b>Our Hiring Process&nbsp;</b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We intentionally conduct a rigorous hiring process, as we want to be absolutely confident that we are hiring the best educators to serve our students &ndash; ones who will thrive at Saigon Star and in Vietnam; who are adaptable and resilient; who are collaborative and professional; who are genuinely caring and passionate about working with children; and committed to lifelong learning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We also strive to conduct an inclusive process that involves many stakeholders, which reflects our commitment to operate as a collaborative community. During this hiring process, we hope that successful applicants learn as much about us, as we learn about them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-&nbsp; Application Screening</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-&nbsp; A short 10-15 minute telephone interview with the Headteacher of Head of Department</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- References requested</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;- Applicant tasks e.g. reading our learning policy, and sending supporting information such as examples of planning, assessments, parent communications and photos of your classroom</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- First full-length interview with members of our leadership team</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;- A final interview (where possible, this will include members of student council and parent community)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;-Formal offer and contracting</p>\r\n\r\n<p>N.B. All positions of employment are dependent on comprehensive criminal and professional background checks. In order to receive a valid work permit and temporary residence card, applicants will be required to submit copies of their degree and teaching credentials for Vietnamese officials to check that you meet the minimum criteria.</p>', 'published', '2020-02-28 03:47:11', '2020-03-02 23:51:17'),
(6, 'Teacher Vacancies', 'Ho Chi Minh, Viet Nam', 'Negotiable', '<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\">Recruitment</span></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>As a growing school, we are always looking to hear from high-quality teachers. If you feel you would be a good addition to the Saigon Star family, please send an up-to-date CV, covering letter and recent photograph to the Headteacher, Mr. James Quantrill, email:&nbsp;james@sgstar.edu.vn</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applicants must hold Qualified Teacher Status (QTS) and have a minimum of three years teaching experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-left: 320px;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#16a085;\">Teacher Vacancies</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 280px;\">* Vietnamese Language Teacher</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 280px;\">* Middle Years Maths, History and Art Teacher (Maternity Cover):<br />\r\nStart Date: 15th March 2020<br />\r\nEnd Date: 3rd July 2020</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 280px;\">* Part-Time Mandarin Language Teacher (Monday - Wednesday):<br />\r\nStart Date: Monday 9th December 2019</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-left: 320px;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#16a085;\">Other Vacancies</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 280px;\">Learning + Teaching Assistant</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 280px;\">Start Date: ASAP Contract Type: Full-time:</p>', 'published', '2020-03-04 00:46:58', '2020-03-04 00:46:58'),
(7, 'Early Years Teaching Assistant (Maternity cover)', 'Ho Chi Minh, Viet Nam', 'Negotiable', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#16a085;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Early Years Teaching Assistant (Maternity cover)</span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Teaching Assistant supports the teachers in enabling the pupils to gain independence and participate fully in the curriculum and general life of the school:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Support pupils during lessons as directed by the class teacher.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Supervise and teach individual, pairs or groups of children as required by the class teacher or line manager.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Be aware, in advance of the teacher&rsquo;s weekly planning.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Contribute to the planning of lessons.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Assist in lesson preparation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Provide feedback to the teacher regarding the performance of pupils the TA has been assigned to work with during a lesson.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Supervise pupils in communal areas to ensure a high standard of behaviour is maintained.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Assist with the supervision of snack times and carry out allocated playground, lunchtime and after-school duties as agreed.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;▪ Organise - and have responsibility for - two Curriculum Option Lessons each term.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;▪ Assist the teacher in displaying and removing pupils&rsquo; work.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;▪ Reward and sanction children in accordance with the school&rsquo;s &lsquo;Positive Behaviour&rsquo; policy to ensure the school&rsquo;s high standards of behaviour and discipline are maintained.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ Collect notices, reply slips etc. Collate and send to office when required.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; ▪ To undertake any other reasonable task as instructed by the Senior TA or any line managers</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp; Full Time&nbsp;| Permanent | Closing date: 29/02/2020</span></p>', 'published', '2020-03-04 00:48:54', '2020-06-07 20:29:23');
